07/03/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The ruling New Democracy (ND) party is maintaining its lead over other parties, according to a survey conducted by the Opinion agency in early March.
According to results released at the weekend, ND has 36.1 per cent support, compared to 32 per cent for the major opposition party PASOK.
The Communist Party of Greece is in third place with 5.9 per cent, while the Coalition of the Left, Movements and Ecology has 3.7 per cent support.
(ANA, Hellenic Radio - 06/03/05)
